---
import LegalDoc from "@layouts/LegalDoc.astro";
import { COHORT } from "@lib/data/cohort";
---

<LegalDoc
  title="Privacy Policy · Build Space"
  description="How Build Space collects, uses, and protects the personal information of parents and students, in line with India's data protection law."
  heading="Privacy Policy"
  lastUpdated="10 June 2026"
>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Build Space</strong> ("Build Space",
    "we", "us", or "our") collects, uses, shares, and protects personal
    information when you visit <a href={COHORT.url}>{COHORT.url}</a> (the "Site") or
    enrol in our Logic Labs cohort (the "Programme"). We operate in India and
    follow the Digital Personal Data Protection Act, 2023 (the "DPDP Act") and the
    Information Technology Act, 2000 and its rules.
  </p>

  <div class="legal-callout">
    Our Programme is for students in Class 9 to 12, many of whom are under 18.
    Accounts are created and payments are made by a parent or legal guardian. By
    using this Site or enrolling a child, you confirm you are the parent or legal
    guardian and you consent to this Policy on your child's behalf.
  </div>

  <h2>1. Information we collect</h2>
  <p>We collect only what we need to run the Programme and the Site:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Information you give us.</strong> When you apply, book the ₹99 demo
      class, or enrol, we collect the parent's name, email address, phone or
      WhatsApp number, the student's first name, the student's school class, and
      what the student already knows or wants to build.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Payment information.</strong> Payments are processed by our payment
      gateway, Razorpay. We do not see or store your full card number, UPI PIN, or
      bank credentials. We receive only a transaction reference, the amount, and
      the payment status.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Information collected automatically.</strong> Like most websites, we
      collect device and usage data — IP address, browser type, pages viewed,
      and how you interact with the Site — through cookies and similar tools.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Communications.</strong> If you email or message us, we keep that
      correspondence so we can respond and keep a record.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. How we use your information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To process the ₹99 demo class booking and cohort enrolment.</li>
    <li>To deliver the Programme — sending join links, schedules, and recordings.</li>
    <li>To contact parents about the class, scholarships, and logistics.</li>
    <li>To take payments and keep accounting and tax records.</li>
    <li>To understand how the Site is used and improve it.</li>
    <li>To meet our legal and regulatory obligations.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Cookies and analytics</h2>
  <p>
    We use cookies and third-party analytics to understand how visitors use the
    Site so we can improve it. These tools may record pages viewed, clicks, and
    anonymised session activity (such as heatmaps). The services we use include:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Hotjar / Contentsquare</strong> — heatmaps and aggregated session analytics.</li>
    <li><strong>Meta Pixel</strong> — measuring the performance of our advertising.</li>
    <li><strong>Google</strong> — analytics and conversion measurement.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    You can block or delete cookies in your browser settings. Some parts of the
    Site may not work as well if you do. We do not use these tools to build a
    profile of any individual student.
  </p>

  <h2>4. How we share information</h2>
  <p>
    We do not sell your personal information. We share it only with service
    providers who help us run the Programme, and only as far as needed:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Razorpay</strong> — to process payments.</li>
    <li><strong>Communication tools</strong> — email and WhatsApp, to reach you.</li>
    <li><strong>Hosting, analytics, and video platforms</strong> — to run the Site and the live classes.</li>
    <li><strong>Authorities</strong> — where we are required to by law.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Children's data</h2>
  <p>
    We take extra care with the personal data of children. We collect a student's
    data only with the consent of their parent or legal guardian, we keep it to
    the minimum needed to run the class, and we do not use it for advertising or
    behavioural tracking directed at the child. A parent can ask us to access,
    correct, or delete their child's data at any time using the contact details
    below.
  </p>

  <h2>6. How long we keep data</h2>
  <p>
    We keep personal data only as long as needed for the purposes above, or as
    required by law (for example, payment and tax records must be kept for several
    years). When data is no longer needed, we delete or anonymise it.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
  <p>Subject to the DPDP Act, you may ask us to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Access the personal data we hold about you or your child.</li>
    <li>Correct data that is inaccurate or incomplete.</li>
    <li>Delete data we no longer need to keep.</li>
    <li>Withdraw a consent you previously gave.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    To make a request, email us at
    <a href={`mailto:${COHORT.contact.email}`}>{COHORT.contact.email}</a>. We may
    need to verify your identity before acting on a request.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Data security</h2>
  <p>
    We use reasonable technical and organisational measures to protect personal
    data against loss, misuse, and unauthorised access. No method of transmission
    over the internet is completely secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute
    security.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Changes to this Policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the
    "Last updated" date at the top of this page. Significant changes will be
    communicated to enrolled parents directly.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Contact us</h2>
  <p>
    For any privacy question or request, including grievances about how your data
    is handled, contact our grievance officer:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Email: <a href={`mailto:${COHORT.contact.email}`}>{COHORT.contact.email}</a></li>
    <li>WhatsApp: {COHORT.contact.whatsapp}</li>
    <li>Build Space, India.</li>
  </ul>
</LegalDoc>
